 Hello I am Michelangelo Moggia and this is Analyze a Picture, today I present to you the Mona Lisa by Leonardo, probably the most famous painting in the world, the image is so well known that you risk not appreciating it anymore. 

00:00:19.655 --> 00:00:25.915
 Instead it is a very important work because it is the synthesis of the art of Leonardo. 

00:00:25.915 --> 00:00:33.350
 Certainly there is a portrait of a woman, made around 1503 and perhaps never finished. 

00:00:33.350 --> 00:00:44.806
 Leonardo always took it with him and from time to time he added some brushstrokes: so much so that thanks to X-rays it was discovered that under the current version there are three others. 

00:00:44.806 --> 00:00:53.412
 The woman portrayed is probably Lisa Gherardini, wife of Francesco Del Giocondo, and then Monna Lisa called the Mona Lisa. 

00:00:53.412 --> 00:01:06.583
 However, identification is not certain. Giorgio Vasari, the first art historian, speaks about it, who among other things exalts Leonardo's skill in painting the woman's eyebrows, 

00:01:06.583 --> 00:01:20.425
 but as you well know it has none. The explanation could however be linked to the fact that Leonardo retouched and modified the painting several times as we have seen. 

